data.name: PictureBoxHelpYear.ToolTip
data.value: Start with '>' to get the songs with year greater than the one you specify Example: "> 2000" will get the songs released after the year 2000. You can use other comparison operators. But if you want to get the songs released in a given year, you don't need to specify "= 2000", just type the year.

data.name: PictureBoxHelpPlayCount.ToolTip
data.value: Start with '>' to get the songs with play count greater than the one you specify Example: "> 5" will get the songs with a play count greater than 5. You can use other comparison operators. But if you want to get the songs played an exact number of times, you don't need to specify "= 5", just type the play count.

data.name: PictureBoxHelpChangePlayCount.ToolTip
data.value: Start with '+' or '-' to increase or decrease, respectivel, the play count of the selected songs by the number you specify after. Example: "+5" will increase the selected songs' play count by five. If you want to specify the play count outright, just type in the year or change the written one.

data.name: PictureBoxHelpChangeYear.ToolTip
data.value: Start with '+' or '-' to increase or decrease, respectively, the year of the selected songs by the number you specify after. Example: "+1" will increase the selected songs' year by one. If you want to specify the year outright, just type in the year or change the written one.

data.name: PictureBoxHelpChangeTrackNumber.ToolTip
data.value: Start with '+' or '-' to increase or decrease, respectively, the track number of the selected songs by the number you specify after. Example: "-1" will decrease the selected songs' track number by one. If you want to specify the track number outright, just type in the track number or change the written one.

data.name: PictureBoxChangeDiscNumber.ToolTip
data.value: Start with '+' or '-' to increase or decrease, respectively, the disc number of the selected songs by the number you specify after. Example: "+1" will increase the selected songs' disc number by one. If you want to specify the disc number outright, just type in the disc number or change the written one.

data.name: PictureBoxListBox.ToolTip
data.value: Select the songs you want to change or delete. If you want to delete them simply press the Delete key after selecting the songs you want to delete. After you select the songs, the text boxes on the right will allow you to change the selected songs' details. If they're blank, that means that detail is not equal in all the selected songs, you can still change the detail on all the selected songs.
